<item>
            <title>[LU-11178] ldiskfs osd to use preallocated buffers instead of pagecache when needed</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11178</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description></description>
                <environment>in some cases (SSD?) it makes sense to bypass pagecache to save on related overhead. 1GB/sec IO with 4K pages imply 256K pages/sec to allocate/insert into the cache which can be quite consuming in terms of CPU cycles and locking (especially for shared files).&lt;br/&gt;
</environment>
